properties.name: Jay Obernolte
properties.biography: Jay Obernolte has represented California's 33rd Assembly District since 2014. Before joining the Assembly, he served as the Mayor of Big Bear Lake for four years and on the Board of Directors for the Big Bear City Airport. Obernolte founded his own video game company in 1988. He holds a bachelor's degree in engineering and applied science from the California Institute of Technology, and a master's degree in artificial intelligence from UCLA.
